# 📊 Banking Customer Analysis & Loan Insights

## 📌 Project Overview

This project focuses on analyzing banking customer data to understand patterns behind loan approvals and rejections. The goal is to extract meaningful insights that can help banks make better financial decisions and reduce risk.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

* Analyze customer demographics (age, gender, city)
* Study income and account balance patterns
* Understand factors influencing loan approval
* Identify trends in credit score and loan distribution

---

## 📂 Dataset Information

The dataset contains the following features:

* `customer_id` – Unique ID of customer
* `age` – Customer age
* `gender` – Male/Female
* `income` – Monthly income
* `account_balance` – Current bank balance
* `loan_amount` – Requested loan amount
* `loan_status` – Approved / Rejected
* `credit_score` – Creditworthiness score
* `city` – Customer location

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies Used

* Python 🐍
* Pandas (Data Analysis)
* Matplotlib & Seaborn (Visualization)
* Jupyter Notebook / Google Colab

---

## 🔍 Data Analysis Steps

1. Data Loading and Exploration
2. Data Cleaning (handling missing values, formatting)
3. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
4. Data Visualization
5. Insight Generation

---

## 📈 Key Insights

* Customers with higher income are more likely to get loan approval
* Credit score plays a major role in loan decisions
* Customers with low account balance tend to get rejected
* Most loan approvals are observed in the age group 25–45

---

## 📊 Visualizations Included

* Loan approval count
* Income vs Loan Amount
* Credit Score distribution
* Loan status comparison charts

---

## 🚀 Conclusion

This analysis helps in understanding customer financial behavior and improving loan approval strategies. Banks can use these insights to minimize risk and improve customer targeting.

